<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-08T05:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-08T05:29:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1765</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-08T13:00:00+02:31"><hi rend="italic">May 8,
                                            1918, 1 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 9, 8.46
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>492. From source considered reliable it is learned that <persName corresp="#p_MWC1">Count Mirbach</persName><note n="3" xml:id="d580fn3"><persName corresp="#p_MWC1">Wilhelm, Count von
                                        Mirbach</persName>, German Ambassador to the Russian
                                    Socialist Federated Soviet Republic.</note> has presented an
                                ultimatum to the Soviet authorities stating that if British and
                                French troops do not at once evacuate Murman Peninsula the
                                consequence will be most grave and it will be necessary for Germany
                                to undertake military operations occupying further territory either
                                in the direction of Murmansk or elsewhere.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_PDC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>